quran[7]{c,v,t,f}:
6,95,"Truly it is Allah Who causes the grain {1} and the fruit-kernel to sprout. He brings forth the living from the dead and brings forth the dead from the living. {2} Such is Allah. So whither are you tending in error?",footnotes:1:The one who causes the seed-grain to split open under the surface of the earth and then makes it grow and appear on the surface as a plant is no other than God.|177909:To 'bring forth the living from the dead' means creating living beings out of dead matter. Likewise
6,96,"It is He Who causes the dawn to split forth, and has ordained the night for repose, and the sun and the moon for reckoning time. All this is determined by Allah the Almighty, the All-Knowing."
6,97,"It is He Who has made for you the stars that you may follow the right direction in the darkness of the land and the sea. We have indeed spelled out signs for the people who have knowledge. {1}",footnotes:1:By 'signs' are meant all that support the proposition that there is only one God
6,98,"It is He Who created you out of a single being, {1} and appointed for each of you a time-limit and a resting place. We have indeed spelled out Our signs for those who can understand. {2}",footnotes:1:This means that God caused the human race to originate from one human being.|177912:If one were to observe carefully the creation of the human species
6,99,"And it is He Who has sent down water from the heavens, and thereby We have brought vegetation of every kind, and out of this We have brought forth green foliage and then from it close-packed ears of corn, and out of the palm-tree from the sheath of it - thick clustered dates, hanging down with heaviness, and gardens of vines, and the olive tree, and the pomegranate - all resembling one another and yet so different. Behold their fruit when they bear fruit and ripen! Surely, in all this there are signs for those who believe."
6,100,"And yet, some people have come to associate the jinn with Allah in His divinity, {1} even though it is He Who created them; and in ignorance they impute to Him sons and daughters. {2} He is Holy and Exalted far above that which they attribute to Him.",footnotes:1:Because of man's imaginativeness and superstitious disposition
6,101,"He is the Originator of the heavens and the earth. How can He have a son when He has had no mate? And He has created everything and He has full knowledge of all things."
